11. License FAQ

Can I modify TaktX Engine?
Yes! You can modify, fork, and improve TaktX Engine for any
legitimate purpose including evaluation, testing, research,
and contributions.

What modifications are NOT allowed?
You may not modify the software specifically to bypass the
3-partition limit or other licensing restrictions in
production environments without a commercial license.

Examples of acceptable modifications:
- Performance improvements
- Bug fixes and security patches
- New BPMN features
- Integration enhancements
- Code quality improvements

Examples of prohibited circumvention:
- Removing partition limit validation
- Disabling license checks
- Patching enforcement mechanisms